    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the ASTM F1717 protocol is the FDA-recognised standard method and expanding to additional test conditions is outside the scope of this submission. All quantitative validation metrics (E/uval < 1.96; percentage error < 10%) are satisfied for all three primary QoIs across both laboratories and all three FEA codes in the ensemble. The model ensemble is judged sufficiently credible to support the regulatory decision for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct under static compression-bending loading.",
